<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-16T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-16T03:00:00-05:00" n="517" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/4682:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-16T10:00:00+02:00">July 16,
                                    1940—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 2:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>382. My 366, July 10, 8 p.m. I have learned that the new Russsian
                            Minister here has now assured the German Minister<note n="71" xml:id="d517fn71">Wilhelm Fabricius.</note> that Russia will not go
                            further in Rumania. For what it is worth and insofar as he may be
                            informed of his Government’s real intentions from day to day this is
                            noteworthy in that the declaration was made to the German Minister and
                            by him communicated to his Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>